{"title_page": "Dr. T. Thimmaiah Institute of Technology", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{refimprove|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name              = Dr. T. Thimmaiah Institute of Technology\n| native_name       = Golden Valley Institute of Technology \n| image_name        = Dr T Thimmaiah Institute of Technology - K.G.F.jpg\n| image_size        = \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = \n| latin_name        = \n| motto             = \n| mottoeng          = \n| established       = \n| closed            = \n| type              = \n| affiliation       = \n| endowment         = \n| budget            = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman          = \n| chancellor        = \n| president         = Dr. T. Venkat Vardhan\n| vice-president    = \n| superintendent    = \n| provost           = \n| vice_chancellor   = \n| rector            = \n| principal         = Dr. Syed Ariff\n| dean              = \n| director          = \n| head_label        = \n| head              = \n| academic_staff    = 70\n| administrative_staff  = \n| students          = \n| undergrad         = \n| postgrad          = \n| doctoral          = \n| other             = \n| city              = [[Kolar Gold Fields]]\n| state             = [[Karnataka]]\n| province          = \n| country           = [[India]]\n| coor              = \n| campus            = Oorgaum Post,\n K.G.F. \u2013 563 120, Kolar District\n| former_names      = Golden Valley Institute Of Technology\n| free_label        = \n| free              = \n| colors            = \n| colours           = \n| athletics         = \n| sports            = \n| nickname          = \n| mascot            = \n| affiliations      = [[Visvesvaraya Technological University]]\n| website           = http://drttit.gvet.edu.in/\n| logo              = \n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\nDr. T. Thimmaiah Institute of Technology (Formerly Known as Golden Valley Institute of Technology - GVIT) was started in the year 1986 at Kolar Gold Fields by Dr. T. Thimmaiah, Ph. D., (London), IAS (Retired), as the founder President under the aegis of Golden Valley Educational Trust, with the sole purpose of imparting quality technical education.\n\nDr. T. Thimmaiah Institute of Technology is affiliated to [[Visvesvaraya Technological University|Visvesvaraya Technological University (VTU)]] - Belagavi, Karnataka and is approved by the [[All India Council for Technical Education|All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE)]] - New Delhi\n\n==Campus and location==\nLush green campus, spread over 33,000 sq.mt of land, built with the state-of-the-art infrastructure, that includes Multiple Classroom Blocks, Well Equipped Laboratories, Student Centre & Amphitheatre, Learning Centre with a Digital Library, Wi-Fi, Track & Field for Athletics and Football,Cricket Field, Badminton Court, Fully Equipped Gymnasium and 4 Hostel blocks to accommodate the students and Faculty.\n\n'''Admission procedure'''\n\n==procedure and eyy==\nStudents are admitted on merit, according to the directives of the Government of Karnataka, both under the Government Quota and the Management Quota.\n\nEligibility for admission to B.E. courses is a pass in 10+2 class or equivalent with a minimum 45% in Science group. Mathematics and Physics are compulsory Science subjects. Any other Science subjects like Biology/Bio-technology/Chemistry  can be the Third Science subjects.\n\n===Undergraduate Programs===\n* [[Civil Engineering]]\n* [[Computer Science and Engineering]]\n* [[Electrical and Electronics Engineering]]\n* [[Electronics and Communication Engineering]]\n* [[Mechanical Engineering]] \n* [[Mining Engineering]]\n\n===Postgraduate Programs===\n*PG in [[Machine Design]] (Mechanical)\n*Digital Communications and Networking\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{coord missing|Karnataka}}\n\n[[Category:All India Council for Technical Education]]\n[[Category:Affiliates of Visvesvaraya Technological University]]\n[[Category:Engineering colleges in Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Kolar district]]\n\n\n{{Karnataka-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{refimprove|date=May 2015}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name              = Dr. T. Thimmaiah Institute of Technology\n| native_name       = Golden Valley Institute of Technology \n| image_name        = Dr T Thimmaiah Institute of Technology - K.G.F.jpg\n| image_size        = \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = \n| latin_name        = \n| motto             = \n| mottoeng          = \n| established       = \n| closed            = \n| type              = \n| affiliation       = \n| endowment         = \n| budget            = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman          = \n| chancellor        = \n| president         = Dr. T. Venkat Vardhan\n| vice-president    = \n| superintendent    = \n| provost           = \n| vice_chancellor   = \n| rector            = \n| principal         = Dr. Syed Ariff\n| dean              = \n| director          = \n| head_label        = \n| head              = \n| academic_staff    = 70\n| administrative_staff  = \n| students          = \n| undergrad         = \n| postgrad          = \n| doctoral          = \n| other             = \n| city              = [[Kolar Gold Fields]]\n| state             = [[Karnataka]]\n| province          = \n| country           = [[India]]\n| coor              = \n| campus            = Oorgaum Post,\n K.G.F. \u2013 563 120, Kolar District\n| former_names      = Golden Valley Institute Of Technology\n| free_label        = \n| free              = \n| colors            = \n| colours           = \n| athletics         = \n| sports            = \n| nickname          = \n| mascot            = \n| affiliations      = [[Visvesvaraya Technological University]]\n| website           = http://drttit.gvet.edu.in/\n| logo              = \n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\nDr. T. Thimmaiah Institute of Technology (Formerly Known as Golden Valley Institute of Technology - GVIT) was started in the year 1986 at Kolar Gold Fields by Dr. T. Thimmaiah, Ph. D., (London), IAS (Retired), as the founder President under the aegis of Golden Valley Educational Trust, with the sole purpose of imparting quality technical education.\n\nDr. T. Thimmaiah Institute of Technology is affiliated to [[Visvesvaraya Technological University|Visvesvaraya Technological University (VTU)]] - Belagavi, Karnataka and is approved by the [[All India Council for Technical Education|All India Council for Technical Education (AICTE)]] - New Delhi\n\n==Campus and location==\nLush green campus, spread over 33,000 sq.mt of land, built with the state-of-the-art infrastructure, that includes Multiple Classroom Blocks, Well Equipped Laboratories, Student Centre & Amphitheatre, Learning Centre with a Digital Library, Wi-Fi, Track & Field for Athletics and Football,Cricket Field, Badminton Court, Fully Equipped Gymnasium and 4 Hostel blocks to accommodate the students and Faculty.\n\n<br />\n\n==Admission procedure and eligibility==\nStudents are admitted on merit, according to the directives of the Government of Karnataka, both under the Government Quota and the Management Quota.\n\nEligibility for admission to B.E. courses is a pass in 10+2 class or equivalent with a minimum 45% in Science group. Mathematics and Physics are compulsory Science subjects. Any other Science subjects like Biology/Bio-technology/Chemistry  can be the Third Science subjects.\n\n===Undergraduate Programs===\n* [[Civil Engineering]]\n* [[Computer Science and Engineering]]\n* [[Electrical and Electronics Engineering]]\n* [[Electronics and Communication Engineering]]\n* [[Mechanical Engineering]] \n* [[Mining Engineering]]\n\n===Postgraduate Programs===\n*[[Machine Design]]\n*Digital Communications and Networking\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n{{coord missing|Karnataka}}\n\n[[Category:All India Council for Technical Education]]\n[[Category:Affiliates of Visvesvaraya Technological University]]\n[[Category:Engineering colleges in Karnataka]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Kolar district]]\n\n\n{{Karnataka-university-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rajashekarajith", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dr._T._Thimmaiah_Institute_of_Technology"}
