atinlibrary.com/quintilian/quintilian.institutio1.shtml the Latin Library].\n{{Refend}}\n\n===Secondary sources===\n{{Refbegin|colwidth=30em}}\n* {{cite book | last=Badian | first=Ernst | authorlink=Ernst Badian | editor=Worthington, Ian| title=Demosthenes: Statesman and Orator | publisher=Routledge | year=2002 | chapter= The Road to Prominence | isbn=978-0-203-18769-2}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Blanshard|first1=Alastair J. L.|last2=Sowerby|first2=Tracey A.|title=Thomas Wilson's Demosthenes and the Politics of Tudor Translation|journal=International Journal of the Classical Tradition|volume=12|issue=1|jstor=30222776|date=Summer 2005|pages=46\u201380|doi=10.1007/s12138-005-0010-7}}\n* {{cite book | last=Blass | first=Friedrich | title=Die Attische Beredsamkeit (in German). Third Volume | publisher=B. G. Teubner | year=1887\u20131898}}\n* {{cite book | last=Bolansie | first=J. | title=Herrmippos of Smyrna | publisher=Brill Academic Publishers | year=1999 | isbn=978-90-04-11303-9}}\n* {{cite book|last=Braund|first=David|title=The Cauldron of Ariantas|publisher=Aarhus University Press|year=2003|isbn=978-87-7934-085-5|editor1-first=Pia Guldager|editor1-last=Bilde|editor2-first=Jakob Munk|editor2-last=H\u00f8jte|editor3-first=Vladimir F.|editor3-last=Stolba|chapter-url=http://www.pontos.dk/publications/books/bss-1-files/BSS1_16_Braund.pdf|chapter=The Bosporan Kings and Classical Athens|access-date=19 July 2007|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070928023759/http://www.pontos.dk/publications/books/bss-1-files/BSS1_16_Braund.pdf#|archive-date=28 September 2007|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}\n* {{cite book | last=Burke | first=Edmund M. | title=Classica et Mediaevalia V. 49 edited by Ole Thomsen| publisher=Museum Tusculanum Press | year=1998 | isbn=978-87-7289-535-2 | chapter=The Looting of the Estate of the Elder Pericles | title-link=Classica et Mediaevalia }}\n* {{cite journal|last=Burke|first=Edmund M.|title=The Early Political Speeches of Demosthenes: Elite Bias in 