{"title_page": "Choi Jin-hyuk", "text_new": "{{Korean name|Kim|Choi}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Choi Jin-hyuk\n| image              = 2013.12.31 SBS \uc5f0\uae30\ub300\uc0c1 \ub808\ub4dc\uce74\ud3ab \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601.jpg\n| caption            = Choi Jin-hyuk in December 2013\n| birth_name         = Kim Tae-ho<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sg.style.yahoo.com/news/choi-jin-hyuk-tells-why-he-started-a-061924906.html|title=Choi Jin Hyuk tells why he started a diet & changed his name|date=6 July 2014|website=Star Naver}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1986|2|9}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=609&aid=0000057875|title=\ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601 \u2018\ud669\ud6c4\u2019 \ucd2c\uc601\uc7a5\uc11c 34\ubc88\uc9f8 \uc0dd\uc77c\ub9de\uc774, \ucf00\uc774\ud06c \ub4e0 \uc655\uc2dd[SNS\u2605\ucef7]|date=9 February 2019|website=Newsen|language=ko}}</ref>\n| birth_place        = [[Mokpo]], [[South Jeolla Province]], South Korea\n| occupation         = Actor\n| years_active       = 2006\u2013present\n| agent              = G-Tree Creative\n| spouse             = \n| module             = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes|color=transparent|\n| hangulborn   = {{linktext|\uae40|\ud0dc|\ud638}}\n| hanjaborn    = {{linktext|\u91d1|\u592a|\u660a}}\n| rrborn       = Gim Tae-ho\n| mrborn       = Kim T'aeho\n| hangul       = {{linktext|\ucd5c|\uc9c4|\ud601}}\n| hanja        = !\n| rr           = Choe Jin-hyeok\n| mr           = Ch'oe Chinhy\u014fk\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Choi Jin-hyuk''' ({{Korean|\ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601}}, born '''Kim Tae-ho''') is a South Korean actor. He gained attention for his supporting roles in ''[[Gu Family Book]]'' and ''[[The Heirs]]'', and then went on to star in lead roles in ''[[Emergency Couple]]'', ''[[Pride and Prejudice (2014 TV series)|Pride and Prejudice]]'', ''[[Tunnel (South Korean TV series)|Tunnel]]'', ''[[Devilish Charm]]'' and ''[[The Last Empress (TV series)|The Last Empress]]''.\n\n==Career==\nKim Tae-ho launched his acting career after he won the grand prize in the [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]] [[reality television|reality]] [[talent show]] ''Survival Star Audition'' in 2006.<ref name=fourcharms /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=109&aid=0003527232|title=[\uc2a4\ud0c0\ud1a1\ud1a1] \uc624\ub514\uc158\u2192\ud30c\uc2a4\ud0c0\u2192\uad6c\uc6d4\ub839\u2192\ud130\ub110..'\ud3ec\ud150 \ud130\uc9c4' \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601\u53f2|date=28 April 2017|website=Osen|language=ko}}</ref>\nHe began using the [[stage name]] Choi Jin-hyuk in 2010, prior to the airing of [[Korean drama|family drama]] ''[[It's Okay, Daddy's Girl]]'', in which he was cast in his first leading role.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010102509132194046|title=\uc2e0\uc608 \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601 '\uad1c\ucc2e\uc544 \uc544\ube60\ub538' \uc8fc\uc778\uacf5, \ud30c\uaca9 \ubc1c\ud0c1|date=25 October 2010|work=10Asia|language=ko}}</ref> He also starred in the romantic comedies ''[[I Need Romance]]'' (2011),<ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Ga-on|title=On the set of tvN series ''In Need of Romance''|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2011071215302044399|work=TenAsia|accessdate=2013-02-23|date=12 July 2011}}</ref> and ''[[Ms Panda and Mr Hedgehog]]'' (2012).<ref>{{cite web|last=Suk|first=Monica|title=Super Junior Donghae, Yoon Seung-a's ''Miss Panda, Mr. Hedgehog'' to lift lid in August.|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2012062216311800653|accessdate=2013-02-23|work=TenAsia|date=22 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Ho|first=Stewart|title=Super Junior's Donghae/Choi Jin Hyuk Fans Feed ''Ms. Panda and Mr. Porcupine'' Crew|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/15070/super-juniors-donghaechoi-jin-hyuk-fans-feed-ms-panda-and-mr-porcupine-crew|work=enewsWorld|accessdate=2013-02-23|date=15 September 2012}}</ref> Choi made his big-screen debut in the romance film ''Love Clinique''.<ref>{{citeweb|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=014&aid=0002646480|title=\ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601, \uc601\ud654 \u2018\uc74c\uce58\ud074\ub9ac\ub2c9\u2019 \uce90\uc2a4\ud305 \u2018\uccab \uc2a4\ud06c\ub9b0 \ub370\ubdd4\u2019|date=11 May 2012|website=Financial News|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nHis breakout came in 2013 after a well-received appearance on fantasy-period drama ''[[Gu Family Book]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Shin|first=Young-eun|title=''Gu Family Book'' begins filming with Lee Yeon Hee and Choi Jin Hyuk|url=http://lsgairenint.tumblr.com/post/43723762629/gu-family-book-begins-filming-with-lee-yeon-hee|work=Korea Star Daily|accessdate=2013-02-23|date=20 February 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Jeon|first=Su-mi|title=Choi Jin Hyuk Makes His Exit after Shaking Up Female Viewers on ''Gu Family Book''|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/33571/choi-jin-hyuk-shines-as-lee-seung-gis-father-in-gu-family-book|work=enewsWorld|accessdate=2013-04-11|date=10 April 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Jang|first=Seo-yoon|title=INTERVIEW: Actor Choi Jin-hyuk|url=http://www.tenasia.com/interview-actor-choi-jin-hyuk/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140328114245/http://www.tenasia.com/interview-actor-choi-jin-hyuk/|work=TenAsia|archivedate=2014-03-28|date=9 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=MacDonald|first=Joan|title=Choi Jin Hyuk And Lee Da Hee: The Year Of Their Breakout Performances|url=http://www.kdramastars.com/articles/11366/20131025/choi-jin-hyuk-and-lee-da-hee-the-year-of-their-breakout-performances.htm|work=KDramaStars|accessdate=2014-08-04|date=25 October 2013}}</ref> Afterwards, Choi landed supporting roles in two high-profile projects: writer [[Kim Eun-sook]]'s trendy drama ''[[The Heirs (TV series)|The Heirs]]'', and the action film ''[[The Divine Move]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Jeon|first=Su-mi|title=Choi Jin Hyuk to Join ''The Heirs'' as Lee Min Ho's Brother|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/37528/choi-jin-hyuk-is-confirmed-for-the-heirs|work=enewsWorld|accessdate=2013-05-31|date=31 May 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Jung|first=Si-woo|title=Choi Jin-hyuk to Join Jung Woo-sung's Upcoming Pic|url=http://www.tenasia.com/choi-jin-hyuk-to-join-jung-woo-sungs-upcoming-pic/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140328090130/http://www.tenasia.com/choi-jin-hyuk-to-join-jung-woo-sungs-upcoming-pic/|work=TenAsia|archivedate=2014-03-28|date=25 July 2013}}</ref> His costar in ''The Divine Move'', [[Jung Woo-sung]] also directed him in the [[short film]] ''Beginning of a Dream'' (Choi had joined Jung's agency Red Brick House).<ref>{{cite web|last=Jeon|first=Su-mi|title=Choi Jin Hyuk Stars in a Short Piece Directed by Jung Woo Sung|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/42196/choi-jin-hyuk-and-jung-woo-sung-collaborate-as-actor-and-director-for-samsung|work=enewsWorld|accessdate=2013-07-31|date=31 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/actor-choi-jin-hyuk-in-the-same-agency-as-jung-woo-sung-51494.html|title=\nActor Choi Jin-hyuk in the same agency as Jung Woo-sung|date=7 January 2013|work=Hancinema|publisher=Nate}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, he headlined his first miniseries, the cable romantic comedy/[[medical drama]] ''[[Emergency Couple]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tenasia.com/song-ji-hyo-choi-jin-hyuk-join-1st-script-reading-session-of-new-tvn-series/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140328094802/http://www.tenasia.com/song-ji-hyo-choi-jin-hyuk-join-1st-script-reading-session-of-new-tvn-series/|url-status=dead|archive-date=28 March 2014|title=Song Ji-hyo, Choi Jin-hyuk Join 1st Script Reading Session of New tvN Series|date=24 December 2013|work=TenAsia}}</ref><ref name=fourcharms>{{cite web|last=Choi|first=Eun-hwa|title=Interview: The Four Charms of Choi Jin Hyuk|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/64005/interview-choijinhyuk-and-his-four-charms|work=enewsWorld|accessdate=2014-04-27|date=18 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150503004753/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/64005/interview-choijinhyuk-and-his-four-charms|archive-date=3 May 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Jung|first=Jin-young|title=Interview: Choi Jin Hyuk Constantly Told Himself Song Ji Hyo is Pretty|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/63855/interview-choijinhyuk-talks-about-filming-emergency-couple|work=enewsWorld|accessdate=2014-04-27|date=19 April 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424010535/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/63855/interview-choijinhyuk-talks-about-filming-emergency-couple|archive-date=24 April 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> Choi then returned to network television with a supporting role in ''[[You Are My Destiny (2014 TV series)|You Are My Destiny]]'', a [[remake]] of the [[Fated to Love You (2008 TV series)|2008 Taiwanese drama]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/choi-jin-hyuk-in-love-you-like-fate-69090.html|title=Choi Jin-hyuk in \"Love You Like Fate\"|date=12 May 2014|work=Hancinema|publisher=enews24}}</ref> Another leading role followed with the [[legal drama]] ''[[Pride and Prejudice (2014 TV series)|Pride and Prejudice]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ha|first1=Soo-jung|title=Choi Jin Hyuk and Baek Jin Hee Confirmed for Drama ''Pride and Prejudice''|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/76339/choijinhyuk-and-baekjinhee-to-star-in-pride-and-prejudice|website=enewsWorld|accessdate=2015-06-15|date=19 September 2014}}</ref><ref name=enlisting>{{cite web|last1=Lee|first1=Min-ji|title=Interview: Choi Jin Hyuk Shares Thoughts on Enlisting in the Army|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/85524/interview-choi-jin-hyuk-shares-thoughts-on-enlisting-in-the-army|website=enewsWorld|accessdate=2015-06-15|date=25 January 2015}}</ref> He was also cast in a minor role in the Japanese film ''[[Koisuru Vampire]]'' (\"Vampire in Love\").\n\nChoi went on a hiatus from acting when he enlisted for [[conscription in South Korea|mandatory military service]] on March 31, 2015.<ref name=enlisting /><ref>{{cite web|last1=Hwang|first1=Hye-jin|title=Choi Jin Hyuk Sends His Farewell to Fans Before Enlisting in Army|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/90369/choi-jin-hyuk-sends-his-farewell-to-fans-before-enlisting-in-army|website=enewsWorld|accessdate=2015-06-15|date=31 March 2015}}</ref> He had the option to join the Seoul Police Promotional Team, the theater unit under the [[Seoul Metropolitan Police Agency]], but choose to serve as an active duty soldier.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Ko|first1=Hong-ju|title=Choi Jin Hyuk to Enlist in Police Promotional Team This Year|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/61175/exclusive-choijinhyuk-to-join-the-army-this-year|website=enewsWorld|accessdate=2015-06-15|date=17 March 2015}}</ref> He was discharged from the army after just seven months due to a knee injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/choi-jin-hyuk-discharged-for-medical-reasons-cartilage-damage-87778.html|title=\nChoi Jin-hyuk discharged for medical reasons, cartilage damage|date=22 October 2015|work=Hancinema|publisher=Segye}}</ref> \n\nChoi made his return with the crime thriller ''[[Tunnel (South Korean TV series)|Tunnel]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2017/03/22/0200000000AEN20170322010451315.html|title=New detective show 'Tunnel' hopes to emulate success of 'Voice'|date=22 March 2017|work=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref> which was a hit in China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2017/03/30/0200000000AEN20170330004200315.html|title=New crime show 'Tunnel' abuzz on China's Weibo: agency|date=30 March 2017|work=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref> In 2018, he was cast in the romantic comedy drama ''[[Devilish Charm]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=241&aid=0002783214|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5] \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601\u00b7\uc1a1\ud558\uc724, '\ub9c8\uc131\uc758 \uae30\uc068' \ucd9c\uc5f0\ud655\uc815\u2026\ud558\ubc18\uae30 \ub9cc\ub09c\ub2e4|date=4 May 2018|website=Ilgan Sports|language=ko}}</ref> and mystery thriller series ''[[The Last Empress (TV series)|The Last Empress]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://channels.vlive.tv/EBF267/celeb/0.8088050|title= \"Empress's Dignity\" confirmed the main cast|date=September 4, 2018|website=JTBC}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, Choi was cast in the thriller drama ''[[Justice (2019 TV series)|Justice]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.sbs.co.kr/news/endPage.do?news_id=N1005193618|title=[SBS Star] Choi Jin Hyuk Confirms to Lead an Upcoming Thriller Drama|date=March 26, 2019|website=SBS News}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, Choi starred in the science fiction action drama ''Rugal''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200323000879&np=1&mp=1|title=OCN\u2019s \u2018Rugal\u2019 dabbles in biotech action|date=March 23, 2020|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television series===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Rainbow Romance]]''\n| High school student ([[bit part]])\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]]\n|-\n| 2006\u20132007\n| ''Just Run!''\n| Lee Hyuk-jin\n| rowspan=2|[[KBS2]] \n|-\n| 2007\n| ''[[Drama City]]'' <br/> \"A Neighborhood for Young People\"\n| Kim Byung-yong\n|-\n| 2007\u20132008\n| ''Belle''\n| Oh Jae-hyuk\n| [[KBS1]]\n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Hometown Legends'' \"Nine-tailed Fox\"\n| Hyo-moon\n| rowspan=3|KBS2\n|-\n| 2008\u20132009\n| ''[[My Precious You]]'' \n| Ha Dong-woo\n|-\n| 2009\n| ''Hometown Legends'' \"Come with Me to Hell\"\n| Lee Rang\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Pasta (TV series)|Pasta]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mwave.me/en/news/news/view/88920/Choi-Jin-Hyuk-was-Jealous-of-Lee-Sun-Gyun-Acting-Opposite-Kong-Hyo-Jin-in-%E2%80%98Pasta%E2%80%99|title=Choi Jin Hyuk was Jealous of Lee Sun Gyun Acting Opposite Kong Hyo Jin in \u2018Pasta\u2019|date=10 March 2015|website=Mwave}}</ref>\n| Sunwoo Deok\n| MBC\n|-\n| 2010\u20132011\n| ''[[It's Okay, Daddy's Girl]]''\n| Choi Hyuk-ki\n| [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]]\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[I Need Romance]]''\n| Bae Sung-hyun\n| [[TVN (South Korea)|tvN]]\n|-\n| 2011-2012\n| ''[[My Daughter the Flower]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.edaily.co.kr/news/news_detail.asp?mediaCodeNo=258&newsId=01157846596384384|title=\ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601-\uc9c4\uc138\uc5f0-\uc774\uc9c0\ud6c8, SBS \uc0c8 \uc77c\uc77c `\ub0b4\ub538 \uaf43\ub2d8\uc774` \uce90\uc2a4\ud305|date=27 September 2011|website=edaily|language=ko}}</ref> \n| Gu Sang-hyuk\n| SBS\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Ms Panda and Mr Hedgehog]]''\n| Choi Won-il\n| [[Channel A (TV channel)|Channel A]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2013\n| ''[[Gu Family Book]]''\n| Gu Wol-ryung\n| MBC\n|-\n| ''[[The Heirs]]'' \n| Kim Won\n| SBS\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2014\n| ''[[Emergency Couple]]''\n| Oh Chang-min\n| rowspan=2|tvN\n|-\n| ''[[Flower Grandpa Investigation Unit]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000494867|title=\uaf43\ud560\ubc30 \uc218\uc0ac\ub300 \ucd5c\uc9c4\ud601 \uae5c\uc9dd\ub4f1\uc7a5\uc5d0, \ub124\ud2f0\uc98c \"\ubc18\uac11\ub2e4\"|date=14 June 2014|website=TV Report|language=ko}}</ref>\n| young Lee Joon-hyuk ([[cameo appearance|cameo]])\n|-\n| ''[[You Are My Destiny (2014 TV series)|You Are My Destiny]]''\n| Daniel Pitt\n| rowspan=2|MBC\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| ''[[Pride and Prejudice (2014 TV series)|Pride and Prejudice]]''\n| Gu Dong-chi\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Tunnel (South Korean TV series)|Tunnel]]''\n| Park Gwang-ho \n| [[Orion Cinema Network|OCN]]\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Devilish Joy]]''\n| Gong Ma-seong\n| [[Maeil Broadcasting Network|MBN]], Dramax\n|-\n| 2018\u20132019\n| ''[[The Last Empress (TV series)|The Last Empress]]''\n| Na Wang-sik / Cheon Woo-Bin\n| SBS\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Justice (2019 TV series)|Justice]]''\n| Lee Tae-kyung\n| KBS2\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Rugal (2020 TV series)|Rugal]]''\n|Kang Ki-Beom\n| OCN\n|}\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \n|-\n! width=10|Year\n! Title\n! Role\n|-\n| 2012 || ''Love Clinique'' || Park Min-soo\n|-\n| 2013 |